IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. SIMPLE-FILE-MOVER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.

* This program moves a file from one location to another.
* It is designed to demonstrate the intricacies of file handling.
* The program is verbose and detailed to ensure clarity.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'input.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'output.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-EOF-FLAG PIC X VALUE 'N'.
    88  EOF-TRUE VALUE 'Y'.
    88  EOF-FALSE VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-COUNTER PIC 9(5) VALUE 0.
01  WS-TEMP PIC X(100).
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR PIC X(100) VALUE 'Frodo'.
01  WS-ANOTHER-UNUSED-VAR PIC X(100) VALUE 'Gandalf'.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    PERFORM INITIALIZE.
    PERFORM OPEN-FILES.
    PERFORM UNTIL EOF-TRUE
     READ INPUT-FILE INTO INPUT-RECORD
         AT END
          SET EOF-TRUE TO TRUE
         NOT AT END
          MOVE INPUT-RECORD TO OUTPUT-RECORD
          PERFORM WRITE-OUTPUT
          ADD 1 TO WS-COUNTER
     END-READ
    END-PERFORM.
    PERFORM CLOSE-FILES.
    STOP RUN.

INITIALIZE.
    * Initialize variables and flags
    MOVE 'N' TO WS-EOF-FLAG.
    MOVE 0 TO WS-COUNTER.

OPEN-FILES.
    * Open the input and output files
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE.
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE.

WRITE-OUTPUT.
    * Write the record to the output file
    WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD.

CLOSE-FILES.
    * Close the input and output files
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE.
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE.

